  The{Domesday Book of 1086}mentions a{
{church}in{Treeton.}Before that the    
 first church on the present site was  
 built in{timber}by{Morcar,}a Saxon    
 Lord. The present stone church was    
 built in the{12th and 13th centuries.}
 It was named after{Helen}who was the  
 mother of{Constantine,}Roman Emperor. 
 The{Brampton Chapel}was added by the  
 people of Brampton for their own use. 
 The{font}has been in use baptising    
 babies for 500 years. The present{    
{Rector,}inducted in 1985, is the Rev. 
 A. Lacey. {DAME SCHOOL  }The former{  
{cottage school}stands almost in{      
{St.Helens churchyard}near the stocks. 
 This provided a{basic education}for a 
 number of{poor children.}In{1846 a    
{Dame Widdowson,}had charge of{8 boys} 
 and{13 girls.}The cottage is now a{   
{private dwelling.}
